                            <p>Lufthansa, officially known as Deutsche Lufthansa A. G., is a well-known airline which serves as the flag carrier of Germany. The airline was established over a hundred years ago, in the year 1917 as Deutsche Luft–Reederei. It has diligently provided high-quality services to the nation since it commenced operations in 1919. </p>
                            <p>The airline changed its name to Deutsche Luft Hansa in 1926 and since then continued in that name. The airline has received global acclaim and a reputation as one of the largest European airlines in terms of both revenue and passengers carried. It has simultaneously carved a name for itself in the world at large with its efficient service. </p>
                            <h2>Lufthansa Airlines Flights</h2>
                            <p>Lufthansa Airlines flights are mostly purchased from the Airbus aerospace corporation. The airlines use both wide-body and narrow-body aircraft of the said aircraft provider. In addition to this, Lufthansa also utilizes Boeing aircraft for wide-body flights. Lufthansa Airlines fleet has been composed of seven different airline families with two of them being from Boeing and the rest from Airbus. </p>
                            <p>Lufthansa flights follow a unique tradition of naming their aircraft after German cities. This was started in September 1960 and the first of these flights was named after Berlin. The tradition continued and till 2010 almost all major aircraft of the company were named after major cities in Germany with a few exceptions. </p>
                            <p>The exceptions included Airbus A321 – 100 which was named after a quarter of Germany and Airbus A340 – 300 which was named after two Canadian cities which had provided shelter to Lufthansa flights during an emergency. Later, it was decided that most aircraft would be known as Star Alliance hub cities except those which had been named after Lufthansa hub cities. </p>
